Here is a Java solution that checks if an integer is a power of three:

```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n = n / 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

This solution works by continuously dividing the input number `n` by 3 as long as it is divisible by 3. If `n` becomes 1, it means it is a power of three. If `n` becomes something other than 1, it means it is not a power of three.

